text: National Highway 166D, commonly referred to as NH 166D is a national highway in India. It is a secondary route of National Highway 66. NH-166D runs in the state of Maharashtra in India. == Route == NH166D connects Pen, Ransai and Madh in the state of Maharashtra. == Junctions == : Terminal near Pen. : Terminal near Madh. == See also == * List of National Highways in India * List of National Highways in India by state == References == == External links == * NH 166D on OpenStreetMap Category:National highways in India Category:National Highways in Maharashtra
